546
00:43:45,398 --> 00:43:46,727
<i>... don't do that.</i>

547
00:43:46,859 --> 00:43:48,852
Ah.

548
00:43:48,987 --> 00:43:53,033
Most deaths, <i>9</i>. Rome versus Pittsburgh,
December last year.

549
00:43:53,160 --> 00:43:55,070
The greatest number of players...

550
00:43:55,204 --> 00:43:59,038
...put out of action
by a single player in a single game...

551
00:43:59,169 --> 00:44:00,580
<i>... 13.</i>

552
00:44:00,712 --> 00:44:03,549
<i>A world record,</i> courtesy of your dear self.

553
00:44:03,675 --> 00:44:06,631
<i>There have been studies</i>
<i>of stat freaks in rollerball.</i>

554
00:44:06,763 --> 00:44:10,597
<i>Some go to the track, but they never</i>
<i>take their eyes off the big board.</i>

555
00:44:10,727 --> 00:44:11,723
What's this?

556
00:44:11,854 --> 00:44:14,690
<i>I've always wondered if a rollerball player...</i>

557
00:44:14,816 --> 00:44:16,893
<i>... sees himself as a class apart.</i>

558
00:44:17,028 --> 00:44:18,856
"Hello."

559
00:44:18,989 --> 00:44:21,030
"Pause."

560
00:44:21,702 --> 00:44:24,953
"I'm Jonathan E. Smile."

561
00:44:26,333 --> 00:44:29,786
"I would like..." This, uh, this for me?

562
00:44:29,922 --> 00:44:32,628
<i>Very astute. Yes.</i>

563
00:44:32,759 --> 00:44:35,133
<i>It's your retirement announcement.</i>

564
00:44:35,973 --> 00:44:39,426
<i>Your special is already scheduled</i>
<i>and announced all over the world.</i>

565
00:44:39,561 --> 00:44:42,267
<i>You're supposed to read this</i>
<i>as part of the programme.</i>

566
00:44:42,399 --> 00:44:44,688
