701
00:57:21,221 --> 00:57:24,472
It's hard finding anything out, Jonathan,
you know that.

702
00:57:24,601 --> 00:57:29,063
Hell, nobody even knows the names
of the men on the directorate any more.

703
00:57:35,492 --> 00:57:37,532
Look, I'm sorry.

704
00:57:40,833 --> 00:57:44,120
- They want you out. You know that?
- Yeah.

705
00:57:44,713 --> 00:57:47,288
But do you know who they are?

706
00:57:47,426 --> 00:57:49,669
- Bartholomew, I guess.
- Mm-mm.

707
00:57:49,804 --> 00:57:51,845
Above Bartholomew.

708
00:57:52,308 --> 00:57:54,765
It's the Executive Directorate.

709
00:57:54,895 --> 00:57:58,266
- Why would they worry about me?
- Well, they do.

710
00:57:58,400 --> 00:58:02,447
They're even after the old man because
he didn't get your retirement announced.

711
00:58:02,573 --> 00:58:05,694
How come they put
the programme on without it?

712
00:58:05,828 --> 00:58:09,910
I think they had to.
They didn't want to. It's very tricky.

713
00:58:12,170 --> 00:58:15,671
Jonathan, there's one thing
you ought to know.

714
00:58:17,219 --> 00:58:21,171
Look, nobody's said it, but I'm sure of it.

715
00:58:21,309 --> 00:58:22,305
Hm?

716
00:58:25,899 --> 00:58:28,356
They're afraid of you, Jonathan.

717
00:58:28,945 --> 00:58:30,985
All the way to the top, they are.

718
00:58:44,301 --> 00:58:46,923
What are they afraid of me for?

719
00:59:04,873 --> 00:59:07,709
Oh, no, don't go yet.
We're showing some replays.

720
00:59:07,835 --> 00:59:09,745
Let's see 'em then!

721
00:59:11,215 --> 00:59:13,256
<i>(crowd roars)</i>

722
01:00:05,712 --> 01:00:08,121
Mr Bartholomew would like to see you now.

723
01:00:08,257 --> 01:00:09,456
He's in the study.

724
01:00:34,963 --> 01:00:37,004
Come on, hurry up, over there!

725
01:00:46,981 --> 01:00:50,601
You know I've always considered
your situation, Jonathan...

726
01:00:50,736 --> 01:00:52,979
...and your needs.

727
01:00:53,115 --> 01:00:55,738
Now you have to consider mine...

728
01:00:55,869 --> 01:00:59,286
...and ours.
- I'm considering it, Mr Bartholomew.

729
01:00:59,416 --> 01:01:02,502
No player is greater than the game itself.

730
01:01:02,754 --> 01:01:05,329
It's a significant game in a number of ways.

731
01:01:05,466 --> 01:01:09,252
The... velocities of the ball,
the awful physics of the track.

732
01:01:09,389 --> 01:01:13,720
And in the middle of it all, men,
playing by an odd set of rules.

733
01:01:13,854 --> 01:01:17,805
It's not a game a man is supposed
to grow strong in, Jonathan.

734
01:01:17,943 --> 01:01:19,984
You appreciate that, don't you?

735
01:01:20,113 --> 01:01:22,153
More and more, Mr Bartholomew.

736
01:01:22,283 --> 01:01:23,908
<i>(laughter)</i>

737
01:01:27,040 --> 01:01:29,080
Shoot that statue!

738
01:01:29,210 --> 01:01:31,880
That's the one! Shoot that!

739
01:01:32,590 --> 01:01:34,630
Hey, the tree!

740
01:01:37,597 --> 01:01:39,637
You must take good advice.

741
01:01:39,934 --> 01:01:43,719
You're not to play against Tokyo.
You're not to play again.

742
01:01:45,024 --> 01:01:47,896
- I want some concessions.
- Concessions?

743
01:01:48,029 --> 01:01:52,408
Believe me, I'd be happy to talk a deal,
Jonathan. I love deals.

744
01:01:52,535 --> 01:01:55,871
But this situation is much, much simpler.

745
01:01:56,166 --> 01:01:59,370
This Multivision event tonight
was very embarrassing.

746
01:01:59,504 --> 01:02:01,747
For me and for others.

747
01:02:02,133 --> 01:02:03,758
Yeah.

748
01:02:04,637 --> 01:02:09,265
It might be I won't ever find out
why I've been asked to leave the game...

749
01:02:09,686 --> 01:02:13,637
...but I do know I can get
some concessions, and I want 'em.

750
01:02:23,452 --> 01:02:24,781
You missed!

751
01:02:26,706 --> 01:02:31,534
I wanna see Ella, my wife.
Arrange it so I can see her again.

752
01:02:31,669 --> 01:02:33,413
That's not easy, Jonathan.

753
01:02:33,546 --> 01:02:35,373
I want other concessions, too,
Mr Bartholomew.

754
01:02:46,643 --> 01:02:49,478
Oh! Oh-ho! Look at that!

755
01:02:49,604 --> 01:02:51,846
<i>(laughter and chatter)</i>

756
01:03:01,950 --> 01:03:05,734
I've never seen anything like that
in my life! That's incredible!

757
01:03:07,372 --> 01:03:09,281
That's terrific.

758
01:03:09,416 --> 01:03:10,744
Look at all the flames!

759
01:03:10,876 --> 01:03:12,915
Specifically, you're bargaining...

760
01:03:13,044 --> 01:03:16,164
...for the right to stay in
a horrible social spectacle.

761
01:03:16,298 --> 01:03:20,461
It has its purposes.
You've served those purposes brilliantly.

762
01:03:21,011 --> 01:03:23,003
Why argue when you can quit?

763
01:03:23,138 --> 01:03:27,005
And you say you want to know
why decisions are made.

764
01:03:27,351 --> 01:03:29,308
Your future comfort is assured.

765
01:03:29,436 --> 01:03:31,345
You don't need to know.

766
01:03:31,480 --> 01:03:35,691
Why argue about decisions you're not
powerful enough to make for yourself?

767
01:03:42,491 --> 01:03:45,278
Energy will treat you well, you know that.

768
01:03:53,961 --> 01:03:58,623
If the rule changes stay the same,
Mr Bartholomew...

769
01:03:58,757 --> 01:04:00,916
...I'm playing with my team.

770
01:04:01,051 --> 01:04:04,088
Too late. The rule change
is scheduled and announced.

771
01:04:04,221 --> 01:04:06,759
There's no going back. You've seen to that.

772
01:04:06,891 --> 01:04:08,171
I'll see you in Tokyo.

773
01:04:10,144 --> 01:04:12,433
You could be made to quit!
You could be forced!

774
01:04:12,563 --> 01:04:13,891
You can't make me quit!

775
01:04:15,983 --> 01:04:17,727
Don't tell me I can't.

776
01:04:17,860 --> 01:04:19,402
Don't ever say that! I can!

777
01:04:19,528 --> 01:04:23,443
- (crowd chants) <i>Jonathan! Jonathan!</i>
- You can be stopped!

778
01:04:23,574 --> 01:04:26,659
(crowd chants)
<i>Jonathan! Jonathan! Jonathan! Jonathan!</i>

779
01:04:26,786 --> 01:04:29,324
<i>Jonathan! Jonathan! Jonathan!</i>

780
01:04:29,664 --> 01:04:32,415
<i>Jonathan! Jonathan! Jonathan!</i>

781
01:04:32,542 --> 01:04:35,661
<i>Jonathan! Jonathan! Jonathan! Jonathan!</i>

782
01:04:40,091 --> 01:04:42,463
- <i>(laughter)</i>
- You are silly!

783
01:04:42,593 --> 01:04:44,633
You could have killed someone!

784
01:04:53,146 --> 01:04:57,060
- It's all going too fast. I'm not packed...
- Forget it, you're not going, Daph.

785
01:04:57,192 --> 01:04:59,683
Those bags are ready.
Here. Take this extra hat.

786
01:04:59,819 --> 01:05:00,733
Sir...

787
01:05:00,862 --> 01:05:03,151
...I've had a call. I have to go over to Energy.

788
01:05:03,281 --> 01:05:06,152
- You're not going to Tokyo?
- What do you mean I'm not going?

789
01:05:06,284 --> 01:05:07,909
I hope this isn't inconvenient.

790
01:05:09,454 --> 01:05:11,910
No, no, it's no... no problem.

791
01:05:12,999 --> 01:05:15,039
I'm supposed to go with you.

792
01:05:15,961 --> 01:05:18,000
Well, what's that mean?

793
01:05:20,215 --> 01:05:23,750
Who, uh, who told you
you're supposed to go with me? Hm?

794
01:05:23,885 --> 01:05:25,925
Nobody told me.

795
01:05:28,056 --> 01:05:32,006
Listen, Jonathan,
I really wanna go with you. I do really.

796
01:05:32,144 --> 01:05:33,887
You'll need me.

797
01:05:34,020 --> 01:05:36,594
Get yourself another assignment,
will you, Daph?

798
01:05:36,732 --> 01:05:39,483
Everybody's an assignment.
Life's an assignment.

799
01:05:39,609 --> 01:05:40,605
Get going.

800
01:05:45,073 --> 01:05:48,692
You'd better do as you're told, Jonathan.
That's all I have to say.

801
01:05:49,828 --> 01:05:51,868
Are you threatening me?

802
01:05:52,664 --> 01:05:54,906
Don't be here when I come back.

803
01:05:55,042 --> 01:05:57,118
You won't be back, Johnny boy...

804
01:05:58,378 --> 01:06:01,830
Don't try to frighten me, Daphne,
you don't know how.

805
01:06:01,965 --> 01:06:02,961
Look...

806
01:06:03,384 --> 01:06:07,880
...you go tell them people that
I'm going to Tokyo and you're not, huh?

807
01:06:08,013 --> 01:06:10,053
You tell 'em that.

808
01:06:10,558 --> 01:06:11,340
Ciao.

809
01:06:11,475 --> 01:06:13,100
Oh!

810
01:06:28,451 --> 01:06:29,446
Keller.

811
01:06:36,542 --> 01:06:39,294
Make sure my gear gets to the track in Tokyo.

812
01:06:39,420 --> 01:06:41,994
I'm gonna travel with the team this trip.

813
01:06:42,131 --> 01:06:44,622
You, uh, call transportation and tell 'em.

814
01:06:44,759 --> 01:06:46,586
Yes, sir.

815
01:07:03,486 --> 01:07:06,024
<i>(crowd chants)</i> Jonathan! Jonathan!

816
01:07:06,155 --> 01:07:08,195
Jonathan! Jonathan!

817
01:07:08,324 --> 01:07:12,405
Jonathan! Jonathan! Jonathan!

818
01:07:12,537 --> 01:07:14,364
Jonathan! Jonathan!

819
01:07:14,497 --> 01:07:17,701
What chance does Houston have
of defeating Tokyo tonight?

820
01:07:17,834 --> 01:07:22,163
Well, uh, both teams have fine players,
and, uh, different styles.

821
01:07:22,297 --> 01:07:23,839
What do you say, Moonpie?

822
01:07:23,965 --> 01:07:26,456
Yeah, yeah, but it's not
an even match, see...

823
01:07:26,593 --> 01:07:30,293
...because the Tokyo team
has all these little short guys.

824
01:07:32,516 --> 01:07:34,888
<i>(crowd chants)</i> Tokyo! Tokyo!

825
01:07:35,018 --> 01:07:38,102
Tokyo! Tokyo! Tokyo!

826
01:07:38,230 --> 01:07:40,269
What about the rule changes?

827
01:07:40,774 --> 01:07:44,772
Well, at Houston, uh,
we kinda play a wide-open system.

828
01:07:44,903 --> 01:07:48,354
Will you comment on a game
where the rules are always changing?

829
01:07:48,490 --> 01:07:51,941
The game's always had rule changes.
They don't affect the good teams.

830
01:07:52,077 --> 01:07:55,280
You're a great new player.
What's the secret of your success?

831
01:07:55,414 --> 01:07:57,869
Oh, it's no secret, I just imitate him...

832
01:07:58,000 --> 01:08:00,621
...and, uh, plastic surgery keeps me beautiful.

833
01:08:00,752 --> 01:08:04,335
There are rumours that the last game
of the season will be played...

834
01:08:04,465 --> 01:08:06,790
...without time limits. Uh, any comments?

835
01:08:07,342 --> 01:08:10,427
I don't think it'll come to that.
It's still a game.

836
01:08:10,554 --> 01:08:13,127
There are also other rumours.
Some say you retired.

837
01:08:13,265 --> 01:08:14,640
Here I am.

838
01:08:14,767 --> 01:08:18,301
<i>(crowds chant)</i>
Jonathan! Jonathan! Jonathan!

839
01:08:18,437 --> 01:08:19,979
Jonathan! Jonathan!

840
01:08:22,608 --> 01:08:25,775
(Bartholomew) <i>Corporate society</i>
<i>was an inevitable destiny...</i>

841
01:08:25,903 --> 01:08:27,942
<i>... a material dream world.</i>

842
01:08:28,072 --> 01:08:31,156
<i>Everything man touched became attainable.</i>

843
01:08:32,076 --> 01:08:34,531
I've been touched all my life.

844
01:08:34,662 --> 01:08:36,701
One way or the other.

845
01:08:37,623 --> 01:08:39,663
Either caressed or hit.

846
01:08:42,586 --> 01:08:45,256
Don't much seem to matter which any more.

847
01:08:47,800 --> 01:08:50,469
I guess that's why I want to see Ella again.

848
01:08:51,095 --> 01:08:53,135
To see if I still feel things now.

849
01:08:55,224 --> 01:08:57,264
You know what I mean?

850
01:09:00,021 --> 01:09:01,645
Yeah...

851
01:09:25,255 --> 01:09:27,543
There are some other things, too.

852
01:09:30,927 --> 01:09:33,383
They took Ella away from me.

853
01:09:36,641 --> 01:09:39,215
Now they're trying to push me out.

854
01:09:42,522 --> 01:09:44,562
I'd sure like to find out why.

855
01:09:51,198 --> 01:09:54,697
I think I'll go to one of them
computer centres.

856
01:09:54,993 --> 01:09:57,033
See what I can find out.

857
01:09:58,872 --> 01:10:00,283
Yeah...

858
01:10:01,917 --> 01:10:04,289
Finding out things, that's, uh...

859
01:10:05,963 --> 01:10:08,418
...that's the thing, Moonpie.

860
01:10:13,720 --> 01:10:18,050
<i>(crowd chants)</i> Jonathan!
Jonathan! Jonathan!

861
01:10:18,183 --> 01:10:21,101
Jonathan! Jonathan!

862
01:10:33,908 --> 01:10:38,237
(announcer) <i>Welcome</i> to <i>Tokyo,</i>
<i>and tonight's dramatic semifinal match...</i>

863
01:10:38,370 --> 01:10:40,908
<i>... for the world's rollerball championship...</i>

864
01:10:41,040 --> 01:10:43,994
<i>... between hosts Tokyo</i>
<i>and the defending champions Houston.</i>

865
01:10:44,126 --> 01:10:46,368
<i>Big rule changes tonight.</i>

866
01:10:46,504 --> 01:10:50,086
<i>There will be no penalties called</i>
<i>and there is limited substitution.</i>

867
01:10:50,216 --> 01:10:52,967
(announcer #2)
<i>Ladies and gentlemen, please stand...</i>

868
01:10:53,094 --> 01:10:56,712
<i>... for the playing of our corporate hymn.</i>

869
01:10:56,847 --> 01:10:58,924
<i>(organ music)</i>

870
01:12:28,649 --> 01:12:30,688
<i>(crowd cheers)</i>

871
01:12:33,237 --> 01:12:36,238
<i>(crowd chants)</i> Houston! Tokyo!
Houston! Tokyo!

872
01:12:36,365 --> 01:12:38,274
<i>(klaxon)</i>

873
01:12:38,409 --> 01:12:40,318
<i>(ball released)</i>

874
01:12:40,452 --> 01:12:43,786
<i>The name of the controller</i>
<i>for tonight's game...</i>

875
01:12:43,914 --> 01:12:45,990
<i>... CC Nakamura.</i>

876
01:12:46,125 --> 01:12:49,410
- You all right?
- <i>(chuckles)</i> Yeah, I'm all right!

877
01:12:49,545 --> 01:12:52,546
I just wanna get out there
and hit them little fellas.

878
01:12:52,673 --> 01:12:53,918
<i>(engines rev)</i>

879
01:12:54,049 --> 01:12:56,256
Listen, stay close now, all right?

880
01:12:56,469 --> 01:12:58,876
Yeah. OK, Johnny. Let's go, let's go!

881
01:12:59,722 --> 01:13:02,213
<i>Attention. Your attention, please.</i>

882
01:13:02,350 --> 01:13:04,841
<i>Rule changes for tonight's game...</i>

883
01:13:04,977 --> 01:13:08,892
<i>... limited substitution and no penalties.</i>

884
01:13:09,023 --> 01:13:11,431
<i>(crowd chants)</i> Jonathan! Jonathan!

885
01:13:11,567 --> 01:13:13,607
Jonathan! Jonathan!

886
01:13:13,736 --> 01:13:14,732
<i>(booing)</i>

887
01:13:14,862 --> 01:13:16,689
<i>(crowd chants)</i> Tokyo! Gambare!

888
01:13:16,823 --> 01:13:18,233
Tokyo!

889
01:13:18,366 --> 01:13:21,236
Gambare! Tokyo! Gambare!

890
01:13:21,369 --> 01:13:24,868
Tokyo! Gambare! Tokyo! Gambare!

891
01:13:29,752 --> 01:13:32,872
<i>(crowd chants)</i> Houston! Houston! Houston!

892
01:13:36,551 --> 01:13:38,294
Haaaaaargh!

893
01:13:38,428 --> 01:13:39,922
<i>(all)</i> Haaaaaargh!

894
01:13:45,852 --> 01:13:47,394
<i>(klaxon)</i>

895
01:13:47,520 --> 01:13:50,355
<i>The controller checks the computer,</i>
<i>ready to fire...</i>

896
01:13:50,482 --> 01:13:53,317
<i>... and the first ball is fired.</i>
<i>The game is under way.</i>

897
01:13:53,443 --> 01:13:55,483
<i>Remember, there'll be no penalties...</i>

898
01:13:55,612 --> 01:13:58,447
<i>... and limited substitution.</i>
<i>This will be a punishing game...</i>

899
01:13:58,573 --> 01:14:00,613
<i>... for both teams.</i>

900
01:14:05,622 --> 01:14:07,698
- Here they come!
- Next time around.

901
01:14:14,297 --> 01:14:16,171
Spread! Spread out!

902
01:14:16,299 --> 01:14:17,877
All right, boys, go ahead.

903
01:14:29,354 --> 01:14:31,394
Tokyo! Gambare!

904
01:14:31,523 --> 01:14:33,101
Stay close now, stay close.

905
01:14:40,407 --> 01:14:41,403
Stick with 'em!

906
01:14:51,669 --> 01:14:53,293
Go, go, go!

907
01:14:56,298 --> 01:14:59,335
<i>There's a scramble in front of the goal.</i>
<i>They all go down.</i>

908
01:14:59,468 --> 01:15:02,042
<i>Kubo, on his knees, scores!</i>

909
01:15:02,179 --> 01:15:04,753
<i>Kubo scores from his kneeling position...</i>

910
01:15:04,890 --> 01:15:06,848
<i>... in front of the goal.</i>

911
01:15:06,976 --> 01:15:10,392
<i>And Tokyo takes a 1-0 lead over Houston.</i>

912
01:15:11,147 --> 01:15:15,892
<i>This is a fast-paced game tonight</i>
<i>with Tokyo leading 1-0.</i>

913
01:15:16,027 --> 01:15:18,565
<i>Houston being pressured</i>
<i>by the faster Tokyo team.</i>

914
01:15:18,696 --> 01:15:20,736
<i>The second ball is fired.</i>

915
01:15:30,249 --> 01:15:31,578
Spread out!

916
01:15:31,709 --> 01:15:32,788
Slow 'em down!

917
01:15:34,670 --> 01:15:36,710
Spread out!

918
01:15:42,095 --> 01:15:45,131
<i>Now the faster tactics of the Tokyo team.</i>

919
01:15:45,265 --> 01:15:48,764
<i>And now, Houston,</i>
<i>their bikers and skaters form a wall.</i>

920
01:15:48,893 --> 01:15:51,265
Tokyo! Gambare!

921
01:15:59,904 --> 01:16:01,731
- Watch the ball!
- Get 'em out!

922
01:16:13,710 --> 01:16:15,750
Bike, bike!

923
01:16:20,091 --> 01:16:22,796
Bike him! Bike him!

924
01:16:23,220 --> 01:16:25,259
You got him, baby...

925
01:16:25,389 --> 01:16:27,298
...you got him.

926
01:16:27,432 --> 01:16:29,472
<i>(crowd roars)</i>

927
01:16:39,069 --> 01:16:41,525
<i>The ball is fired,</i>
<i>and the second period is under way...</i>

928
01:16:41,655 --> 01:16:42,935
<i>... with Tokyo leading.</i>

929
01:16:43,073 --> 01:16:45,860
<i>Houston forced to come</i>
<i>from behind tonight. Houston.</i>

930
01:16:50,581 --> 01:16:52,620
Here you go.

931
01:16:52,833 --> 01:16:55,406
Watch the man behind me!
Watch the man behind me!

932
01:17:03,260 --> 01:17:04,885
<i>(klaxon)</i>

933
01:17:09,809 --> 01:17:11,635
<i>The ball is in play again.</i>

934
01:17:11,769 --> 01:17:14,176
<i>It is scooped up by Carter for Houston.</i>

935
01:17:14,313 --> 01:17:16,222
<i>Houston on the offensive attack.</i>

936
01:17:20,903 --> 01:17:22,314
Whoo!

937
01:17:27,535 --> 01:17:28,566
<i>(booing)</i>

938
01:17:36,919 --> 01:17:38,330
Come on!

939
01:17:40,631 --> 01:17:43,549
<i>(crowd chants)</i> Jonathan! Jonathan!

940
01:17:43,676 --> 01:17:47,460
Jonathan! Jonathan! Jonathan!

941
01:17:50,058 --> 01:17:51,053
Go!

942
01:17:54,103 --> 01:17:57,307
<i>Right in the slot,</i>
<i>through three men and he scores!</i>

943
01:17:58,566 --> 01:18:00,358
<i>Houston goal...</i>

944
01:18:00,485 --> 01:18:03,439
<i>... scored by Jonathan E!</i>

945
01:18:03,571 --> 01:18:06,905
<i>The time - 12.05, second period.</i>

946
01:18:07,033 --> 01:18:09,441
- I love this game!
- Yeah!

947
01:18:12,956 --> 01:18:17,784
<i>Some injuries here as three players</i>
<i>are helped off the track.</i>

948
01:18:24,176 --> 01:18:26,417
- Sprint!
- Yeah, right!

949
01:18:30,932 --> 01:18:32,806
Come on, Moonpie, Moonpie!

950
01:18:32,934 --> 01:18:34,974
Over here! Over here!

951
01:18:37,439 --> 01:18:41,686
- What the hell are those guys doing?
- I don't know. Come on, stay close.

952
01:18:51,119 --> 01:18:53,159
I told you to stay close.

953
01:18:54,873 --> 01:18:57,993
All right, turn loose
next time around, all right?

954
01:18:58,127 --> 01:19:00,415
All right? Go on, go on, go on, go on!

955
01:19:02,297 --> 01:19:03,293
Moonpie!

956
01:19:05,342 --> 01:19:06,718
I got him!

957
01:19:06,844 --> 01:19:08,386
Let me have him!

958
01:19:22,359 --> 01:19:23,355
<i>(klaxon)</i>

959
01:19:32,828 --> 01:19:34,868
Tokyo! Gambare!

960
01:19:35,206 --> 01:19:36,202
Tokyo! Gambare!

961
01:20:04,402 --> 01:20:07,071
Take it easy. Everything will be all right.

962
01:20:07,197 --> 01:20:08,988
Sit down over here.

963
01:20:09,115 --> 01:20:11,950
Sit right here. Everything's gonna be all right.

964
01:20:12,076 --> 01:20:14,828
Medic, hey, medic, come over here! Come on!

965
01:20:41,189 --> 01:20:42,814
- Moonpie!
- <i>(klaxon)</i>

966
01:21:01,710 --> 01:21:04,628
- Come on, Moonpie.
- Come on, get some help!

967
01:21:04,755 --> 01:21:07,424
Set him down, set him down!

968
01:21:18,936 --> 01:21:20,596
Just a bit more.

969
01:21:20,729 --> 01:21:22,354
Breathe.

970
01:21:24,400 --> 01:21:26,309
Come on now, Moonpie.

971
01:21:26,443 --> 01:21:28,483
Come on, Moonpie!

972
01:21:42,960 --> 01:21:47,005
Come on, Tokyo!
Go get 'em! Go, go, go, Tokyo!

973
01:21:50,593 --> 01:21:53,629
Jonathan, watch yourself out there!
Now, watch them!

974
01:21:53,763 --> 01:21:56,384
<i>(crowd chants)</i>
Jonathan! Jonathan! Jonathan!

975
01:21:56,516 --> 01:22:00,430
Jonathan! Jonathan! Jonathan! Jonathan!

976
01:22:00,561 --> 01:22:04,310
Jonathan! Jonathan! Jonathan! Jonathan!

977
01:22:08,027 --> 01:22:09,569
Keep behind, Blue.

978
01:22:09,696 --> 01:22:12,151
<i>(crowd chants)</i> Houston! Houston! Houston!

979
01:22:26,880 --> 01:22:29,252
<i>(crowd chants)</i> Tokyo! Gambare! Tokyo!

980
01:22:55,492 --> 01:22:56,903
<i>(klaxon)</i>

981
01:23:12,885 --> 01:23:14,509
<i>(speaks Japanese)</i>

982
01:23:23,270 --> 01:23:25,310
Look out!

983
01:23:34,657 --> 01:23:35,771
<i>Jonathan E!</i>

984
01:23:35,908 --> 01:23:39,028
<i>Time in the third period, 11.35.</i>

985
01:24:01,350 --> 01:24:02,975
<i>(klaxon)</i>

986
01:24:08,566 --> 01:24:10,606
Sprint! Sprint!

987
01:24:17,033 --> 01:24:18,942
Tokyo! Gambare!

988
01:24:21,913 --> 01:24:23,704
Tokyo! Tokyo!

989
01:24:28,294 --> 01:24:29,872
Roll off! Roll off!

990
01:24:32,841 --> 01:24:33,338
Blue!

991
01:25:06,917 --> 01:25:08,956
This way, please.

992
01:25:20,013 --> 01:25:24,093
May I say first, please,
that you played a superb game in our city.

993
01:25:24,226 --> 01:25:26,265
Thank you.

994
01:25:33,736 --> 01:25:36,690
A simple problem,
yet I know it is difficult for you.

995
01:25:36,822 --> 01:25:39,028
Your team-mate has no family
we can contact...

996
01:25:39,158 --> 01:25:43,736
...and permission is required now
before, uh, before consummating matters.

997
01:25:49,001 --> 01:25:51,041
So, he's, uh, technically dead?

998
01:25:51,170 --> 01:25:53,246
Yes, unfortunately.

999
01:25:53,380 --> 01:25:56,832
His heart and lungs will function,
but his brain is, uh...

1000
01:25:56,967 --> 01:25:58,960
It has expired.

1001
01:25:59,095 --> 01:26:01,764
From the first minutes we had him,
it was hopeless.

1002
01:26:01,889 --> 01:26:06,136
- I believe this was explained to you.
- He's warm.

1003
01:26:06,269 --> 01:26:10,480
Yes. But if you will, please,
you must sign a release form.

1004
01:26:10,606 --> 01:26:11,721
It is required.

1005
01:26:13,901 --> 01:26:15,941
Does he, uh...

1006
01:26:19,907 --> 01:26:21,947
Does he dream?

1007
01:26:22,076 --> 01:26:25,944
No, there is no brain wave at all,
no sort of consciousness.

1008
01:26:26,080 --> 01:26:28,867
Just a deep coma, a vegetable.

1009
01:26:29,000 --> 01:26:31,206
No dreams, nothing.

1010
01:26:32,503 --> 01:26:34,543
But even a...

1011
01:26:36,466 --> 01:26:38,791
...a plant, uh, feels something.

1012
01:26:38,927 --> 01:26:40,718
Who can say? Please.

1013
01:26:40,845 --> 01:26:42,885
It, uh...

1014
01:26:45,433 --> 01:26:47,556
...senses life. I mean, it, um...

1015
01:26:48,895 --> 01:26:50,935
...turns towards the sun.

1016
01:26:52,107 --> 01:26:54,099
It's alive, isn't it?

1017
01:26:54,234 --> 01:26:55,562
You must sign.

1018
01:26:57,445 --> 01:26:59,485
You, uh...

1019
01:26:59,823 --> 01:27:01,862
You just leave him the way he is.

1020
01:27:03,785 --> 01:27:05,825
Just leave him as he is.

1021
01:27:05,954 --> 01:27:08,030
Someone must sign. There's no other way.

1022
01:27:08,165 --> 01:27:10,490
- Arrangements will be made.
- Please...

1023
01:27:10,625 --> 01:27:14,374
...there are hospital rules that...
- No, there aren't.

1024
01:27:14,504 --> 01:27:16,830
There aren't any rules at all.

1025
01:28:02,970 --> 01:28:05,259
Let me know if you have any problems.

1026
01:28:06,348 --> 01:28:08,721
You won't find any answers in Geneva.

1027
01:28:11,103 --> 01:28:13,143
Take care of your arm.

1028
01:28:49,058 --> 01:28:53,139
<i>In my opinion we are confronted here</i>
<i>with something of a situation.</i>

1029
01:28:54,272 --> 01:28:57,890
<i>Otherwise I would not have presumed</i>
<i>to take up your time.</i>

1030
01:28:58,777 --> 01:29:02,477
<i>Once again it concerns</i>
<i>the case of Jonathan E.</i>

1031
01:29:04,032 --> 01:29:08,160
<i>We know we don't want anything</i>
<i>extraordinary to happen to Jonathan.</i>

1032
01:29:08,286 --> 01:29:10,326
<i>We've already agreed on that.</i>

1033
01:29:11,331 --> 01:29:13,787
<i>No accidents, nothing unnatural.</i>

1034
01:29:14,876 --> 01:29:19,503
<i>The game was created to demonstrate</i>
<i>the futility of individual effort.</i>

1035
01:29:20,632 --> 01:29:22,874
<i>Let the game do its work.</i>

1036
01:29:23,802 --> 01:29:27,218
<i>If the Energy Corporation</i>
<i>has done all it can...</i>

1037
01:29:27,347 --> 01:29:31,677
<i>... and if a champion defeats the meaning</i>
<i>for which the game was designed...</i>

1038
01:29:31,810 --> 01:29:34,431
<i>... then he must lose.</i>

1039
01:29:36,106 --> 01:29:38,644
<i>I hope you agree with my reasoning.</i>

1040
01:29:59,838 --> 01:30:02,508
<i>Thank you all.</i>

1041
01:30:58,356 --> 01:31:00,396
Will you follow me, please?

1042
01:31:37,312 --> 01:31:41,642
Hello! Hello! Yes, it is!

1043
01:31:41,775 --> 01:31:44,978
The famous Jonathan E. Oh, hard to believe!

1044
01:31:45,112 --> 01:31:47,021
Ah, sorry things are in a mess.

1045
01:31:47,155 --> 01:31:50,821
The rollerball champion. Hah, wonderful.

1046
01:31:50,951 --> 01:31:53,442
Not many people come to see us, you know.

1047
01:31:53,579 --> 01:31:56,496
We're not easy to talk to, Zero and I.

1048
01:31:56,623 --> 01:31:59,660
We're a little confused again here today.

1049
01:32:00,753 --> 01:32:02,792
This is embarrassing.

1050
01:32:04,006 --> 01:32:06,413
It's embarrassing to misplace things.

1051
01:32:06,550 --> 01:32:08,590
You've misplaced some data?

1052
01:32:08,719 --> 01:32:11,636
Mm, the whole of the 13th century.

1053
01:32:14,308 --> 01:32:18,092
Misplaced the computers,
several conventional computers.

1054
01:32:18,229 --> 01:32:20,055
We can't find them.

1055
01:32:20,564 --> 01:32:24,183
We're always moving things around,
getting organised...

1056
01:32:25,611 --> 01:32:29,525
...my assistants and I.
But this, this is Zero's fault.

1057
01:32:29,699 --> 01:32:33,198
Zero, he's the world's file cabinet.

1058
01:32:33,327 --> 01:32:37,539
Yes, pity. The poor old 13th century.

1059
01:32:41,127 --> 01:32:44,460
Well, come along now.
You want to get started, don't you?

1060
01:32:44,589 --> 01:32:46,628
Yes, sir.

1061
01:32:47,633 --> 01:32:49,673
- Ooh!
- Hm?

1062
01:32:53,848 --> 01:32:55,841
This way.

1063
01:32:55,975 --> 01:32:57,932
Now...

1064
01:32:58,061 --> 01:33:00,552
...we've lost those computers...

1065
01:33:00,688 --> 01:33:03,144
...with all of the 13th century in them.

1066
01:33:03,274 --> 01:33:07,983
Not much in the century,
just Dante, and a few corrupt popes.

1067
01:33:08,112 --> 01:33:11,813
But it's so distracting and annoying.

1068
01:33:11,950 --> 01:33:15,069
You've unlimited restrictions here,
of course...

1069
01:33:15,203 --> 01:33:19,414
...but, uh, you'll have to come
so... so many times.

1070
01:33:19,874 --> 01:33:22,116
It all takes such... such effort.

1071
01:33:22,252 --> 01:33:24,541
Do the, uh, executives still come here?

1072
01:33:24,671 --> 01:33:26,710
Oh, they used to, some of them.

1073
01:33:26,840 --> 01:33:30,291
- What about the books?
- Books, books? They're all changed.

1074
01:33:30,427 --> 01:33:33,131
All transcribed. All information is here.

1075
01:33:33,263 --> 01:33:35,302
We've Zero, of course.

1076
01:33:35,473 --> 01:33:38,558
He's the central brain, the world's brain.

1077
01:33:38,935 --> 01:33:41,605
Fluid mechanics, fluidics.

1078
01:33:42,230 --> 01:33:43,428
He's liquid, you see.

1079
01:33:43,565 --> 01:33:46,234
His... waters touch...

1080
01:33:46,693 --> 01:33:48,733
...all knowledge.

1081
01:33:52,324 --> 01:33:56,535
Everything we ask has become so,
ah, so complicated now.

1082
01:33:56,662 --> 01:33:58,286
Each thing we ask...

1083
01:33:58,413 --> 01:34:01,829
This morning we wanted to know
something about the 13th century.

1084
01:34:01,959 --> 01:34:04,663
He flows out into all our storage systems.

1085
01:34:04,795 --> 01:34:07,998
He considers everything. He's become so...

1086
01:34:08,674 --> 01:34:10,713
...ambiguous now...

1087
01:34:10,843 --> 01:34:13,927
...as if he knows... nothing at all.

1088
01:34:14,054 --> 01:34:16,972
Um, could you tell me something
about the corporate wars?

1089
01:34:17,099 --> 01:34:20,634
Wars, wars?
Oh, yes, of course, we have them all here.

1090
01:34:20,769 --> 01:34:23,640
Punic War, Prussian War,
Peloponnesian War.

1091
01:34:23,772 --> 01:34:27,521
Crimean War, Wars of the Roses.
One doesn't recall them in sequence...

1092
01:34:27,651 --> 01:34:29,977
...but, uh, corporate wars?

1093
01:34:30,112 --> 01:34:34,904
Hm. Well, Zero will or can,
I'm sure, tell you anything.

1094
01:34:44,251 --> 01:34:47,537
A memory pool, you see.

1095
01:34:49,131 --> 01:34:54,090
He's supposed to tell us where things are,
and what they might possibly mean.

1096
01:34:56,138 --> 01:34:58,594
Look, Zero. A visitor.

1097
01:34:59,475 --> 01:35:02,678
Jonathan E, the rollerball champion.

1098
01:35:03,896 --> 01:35:06,981
You've filed away a lot of data on him.

1099
01:35:07,275 --> 01:35:09,314
Do you remember?

1100
01:35:10,695 --> 01:35:13,696
- Does it answer you?
- Oh, yes, it speaks.

1101
01:35:13,823 --> 01:35:15,863
It finds things...

1102
01:35:16,492 --> 01:35:18,532
...and loses them...

1103
01:35:18,745 --> 01:35:21,414
...and confuses itself.

1104
01:35:23,791 --> 01:35:27,410
Ask anything, he'll find it for you,
section and lot...

1105
01:35:28,213 --> 01:35:30,252
...won't you, Zero?

1106
01:35:30,840 --> 01:35:33,711
Well, all right, uh, I'd like, uh...

1107
01:35:35,136 --> 01:35:39,051
I'd like, uh, some information
about corporate decisions...

1108
01:35:39,182 --> 01:35:41,554
How they're made and who makes them.

1109
01:35:46,356 --> 01:35:47,981
Zero...

1110
01:35:48,733 --> 01:35:50,726
...you heard the question.

1111
01:35:50,861 --> 01:35:52,900
- Answer him.
- <i>(beep)</i>

1112
01:35:53,905 --> 01:35:55,364
<i>Negative.</i>

1113
01:35:55,490 --> 01:35:58,859
You don't have to give him
a full political briefing.

1114
01:36:00,120 --> 01:36:01,116
Answer.

1115
01:36:01,246 --> 01:36:02,575
<i>Negative.</i>

1116
01:36:02,706 --> 01:36:04,745
This is Jonathan E.

1117
01:36:05,417 --> 01:36:07,457
He has to know.

1118
01:36:08,170 --> 01:36:10,209
Make it simple.

1119
01:36:11,465 --> 01:36:12,627
Answer.

1120
01:36:12,758 --> 01:36:15,878
<i>Corporate decisions are made</i>
<i>by corporate executives.</i>

1121
01:36:16,011 --> 01:36:19,462
- <i>Corporate executives make...</i>
- We have the answers. We do have them.

1122
01:36:19,598 --> 01:36:22,469
- <i>Knowledge converts to power.</i>
- We're the waters of history.

1123
01:36:22,601 --> 01:36:24,594
<i>Energy equals genius.</i>

1124
01:36:24,728 --> 01:36:26,804
- <i>Power is knowledge.</i>
- I don't want to bully you.

1125
01:36:26,939 --> 01:36:28,978
<i>Genius is energy.</i>

1126
01:36:29,483 --> 01:36:33,563
- <i>Corporate entities control elements...</i>
- You have to answer!

1127
01:36:33,696 --> 01:36:36,613
<i>... of economic life, technology, capital...</i>

1128
01:36:36,740 --> 01:36:40,406
<i>... labour, and markets.</i>
<i>Corporate decisions are made by...</i>

1129
01:36:40,536 --> 01:36:43,027
- You have to, Zero!
- <i>... corporate executives...</i>

1130
01:36:43,164 --> 01:36:44,741
<i>The 13th century...</i>

1131
01:36:44,874 --> 01:36:49,085
- <i>Negative, negative, negative...</i>
- It's so... embarrassing!

1132
01:36:49,211 --> 01:36:51,881
<i>Negative, negative, negative...</i>

1133
01:36:52,006 --> 01:36:54,497
<i>... negative, negative, negative, negative.</i>

1134
01:37:23,162 --> 01:37:25,451
# <i>Albinoni-Giazotto "Adagio"</i>

1135
01:37:25,582 --> 01:37:27,491
Hello, Johnny.

1136
01:37:27,917 --> 01:37:29,957
How are you, Ella?

1137
01:37:31,754 --> 01:37:33,379
Nervous.

1138
01:37:35,884 --> 01:37:37,923
How are you?

1139
01:37:43,475 --> 01:37:46,345
I'm, uh... I'm all right, I guess.

1140
01:37:50,982 --> 01:37:52,560
What are you doing?

1141
01:37:52,692 --> 01:37:54,732
Oh, looking at you.

1142
01:37:56,530 --> 01:37:58,569
Counting your scars.

1143
01:38:00,325 --> 01:38:02,994
Seeing how you've changed.

1144
01:38:03,286 --> 01:38:05,326
Oh, you mean, that's, uh...

1145
01:38:05,455 --> 01:38:08,990
That's how I've changed, huh?
Just a little more beat-up.

1146
01:38:09,126 --> 01:38:11,165
Oh, no!

1147
01:38:11,753 --> 01:38:13,793
You're just not...

1148
01:38:15,340 --> 01:38:17,380
Yeah, well.

1149
01:38:18,427 --> 01:38:20,466
Come on.

1150
01:38:33,692 --> 01:38:35,768
You, uh, want a drink or something?

1151
01:38:35,903 --> 01:38:37,942
No, thank you.

1152
01:38:38,447 --> 01:38:40,605
You have a lovely place.

1153
01:38:40,741 --> 01:38:43,742
Oh, thank you. Well, I've seen your house.

1154
01:38:44,620 --> 01:38:46,659
You have?

1155
01:38:48,582 --> 01:38:51,038
Yeah, uh, when we, uh...

1156
01:38:51,794 --> 01:38:55,163
...played in Rome, I, uh, stood a block away...

1157
01:38:55,297 --> 01:38:57,337
...and, uh...

1158
01:38:58,134 --> 01:39:01,218
...watched your front gate
for a couple of hours.

1159
01:39:04,265 --> 01:39:06,934
<i>(clears throat)</i> I was just, uh...

1160
01:39:09,437 --> 01:39:12,722
...standing there... wondering, uh...

1161
01:39:13,941 --> 01:39:16,397
...what your furniture looked like...

1162
01:39:16,527 --> 01:39:19,279
...what you said to each other
in the mornings.

1163
01:39:21,157 --> 01:39:23,944
Yeah. What's he like? Uh...

1164
01:39:24,077 --> 01:39:26,318
What's he do, this, uh...

1165
01:39:27,413 --> 01:39:29,904
- Oh, he's a city engineer.
- Ah!

1166
01:39:30,792 --> 01:39:32,784
We have a... jet-copter...

1167
01:39:32,919 --> 01:39:34,746
...a son...

1168
01:39:34,879 --> 01:39:37,916
...two cats and a place in the Alps.

1169
01:39:39,634 --> 01:39:42,339
Well, you don't really want to hear all of this.

1170
01:39:43,429 --> 01:39:45,552
A son, huh?

1171
01:39:45,682 --> 01:39:47,306
Yes.

1172
01:39:51,229 --> 01:39:53,269
We have a lot of friends.

1173
01:39:53,773 --> 01:39:57,142
And he has a lover.
We have furniture a lot like yours.

1174
01:39:58,862 --> 01:40:01,946
Same taste in furniture. How about that?

1175
01:40:06,453 --> 01:40:08,576
You know, Johnny...

1176
01:40:08,705 --> 01:40:11,374
...all they want is a kind of incidental control...

1177
01:40:11,500 --> 01:40:13,955
...over just a part of our lives.

1178
01:40:14,085 --> 01:40:16,956
They have control
economically and politically...

1179
01:40:17,089 --> 01:40:19,330
...but they also provide. You know they do.

1180
01:40:19,466 --> 01:40:21,506
Provide, huh?

1181
01:40:25,973 --> 01:40:28,890
They were responsible for taking you away...

1182
01:40:29,017 --> 01:40:31,224
...and I started to hate 'em.

1183
01:40:31,353 --> 01:40:33,393
But they weren't.

1184
01:40:34,147 --> 01:40:36,187
It was the game, Johnny.

1185
01:40:42,823 --> 01:40:44,401
I mean...

1186
01:40:44,533 --> 01:40:46,989
...it was so important to you.

1187
01:40:51,081 --> 01:40:53,323
It was as if I wasn't even there.

1188
01:40:57,379 --> 01:41:00,250
The play, there was nothing else.

1189
01:41:03,010 --> 01:41:05,050
I'm sorry.

1190
01:41:08,599 --> 01:41:11,268
You know I wanted you here.

1191
01:41:11,435 --> 01:41:13,891
Well, I mean...

1192
01:41:14,355 --> 01:41:17,439
...this might sound all wrong, but, um...

1193
01:41:19,193 --> 01:41:21,862
Well, I was just trying to...

1194
01:41:22,738 --> 01:41:24,778
...remember myself then.

1195
01:41:27,869 --> 01:41:29,493
Yeah.

1196
01:41:30,830 --> 01:41:33,499
Maybe it was, uh...

1197
01:41:35,293 --> 01:41:37,962
...Iove I wanted to try to remember.

1198
01:41:54,145 --> 01:41:59,566
Ah, there's a... a lot of things
I want to talk to you about.

1199
01:42:04,155 --> 01:42:05,780
